result.execSummary:
The defendant Rachel C. Mulholland was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Conditions:  

Pay court costs and costs of probation.

Attend, pay for, and successfully complete any educational programs or counseling as ordered by the agent.

The Court recommends discharge of probation after 6 months if Defendant has paid financial obligations and there have been no significant violations of probation.  

DNA sample to be provided at the Richland County Sheriff's Department prior to Defendant signing up for probation.  

2 days credit in the event of revocation.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
